ğŸ“Œ 1. What is RAG?

**RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)** is a technique where:

ğŸ‘‰ An LLM retrieves relevant information
ğŸ‘‰ Then uses that information to generate accurate responses

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  Simple Definition

> RAG = Retrieve relevant knowledge first, then generate response.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“Œ 2. Why Do We Need RAG?

LLMs alone:

* Forget facts
* Hallucinate
* Have limited knowledge cutoff
* Cannot access private documents

RAG solves this by:

âœ” Using external knowledge
âœ” Reducing hallucination
âœ” Accessing real-time or private data
âœ” Improving factual accuracy

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“Œ 3. Traditional LLM vs RAG

| Feature             | Traditional LLM | RAG   |
| ------------------- | --------------- | ----- |
| External Knowledge  | âŒ               | âœ…     |
| Private Data Access | âŒ               | âœ…     |
| Hallucination Risk  | High            | Lower |
| Contextual Accuracy | Limited         | High  |
| Real-Time Updates   | âŒ               | âœ…     |

