```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“Œ 5. RAG Architecture Components

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 5.1 Document Loader

Loads data from:

* PDFs
* Text files
* Websites
* Databases

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 5.2 Text Chunking

Large documents are split into:

* Small chunks (e.g., 500â€“1000 tokens)
* Overlapping segments

Why?

* Improves retrieval accuracy
* Fits model context window

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 5.3 Embedding Model

Converts text into vectors.

Example:

```text
"Agentic AI improves automation"
â†’ [0.21, 0.98, 0.45, ...]
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 5.4 Vector Database

Stores embeddings.

Examples:

* Chroma
* FAISS
* Qdrant

Used for:

* Semantic similarity search

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 5.5 Retriever

Finds most relevant chunks based on query embedding.

---

ğŸ”¹ 5.6 LLM Generator

Receives:

* User question
* Retrieved context

Generates grounded response.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“Œ 6. Full RAG Flow

```text
Step 1: Load documents
Step 2: Split into chunks
Step 3: Generate embeddings
Step 4: Store in vector DB
Step 5: User asks question
Step 6: Convert question to embedding
Step 7: Retrieve similar chunks
Step 8: Send context + question to LLM
Step 9: Generate final answer
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“Œ 7. RAG in Agentic AI

In Agentic AI:

* Agents retrieve knowledge
* Memory is powered by vector DB
* Agents reason with retrieved context
* Tools may update knowledge base

RAG becomes the **long-term memory system**.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“Œ 8. Types of RAG Systems

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 1ï¸âƒ£ Basic RAG

* Single retrieval step
* Simple LLM generation

---

ğŸ”¹ 2ï¸âƒ£ Advanced RAG

* Re-ranking
* Multi-query retrieval
* Hybrid search
* Memory updates

---

ğŸ”¹ 3ï¸âƒ£ Agentic RAG

* Agents decide when to retrieve
* Agents refine queries
* Multi-step retrieval reasoning

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“Œ 9. Common RAG Mistakes

* Not chunking properly
* Too large chunk size
* Poor embedding model
* Not limiting retrieved results
* Ignoring token limits

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“Œ 10. RAG vs Fine-Tuning

| Feature              | RAG               | Fine-Tuning       |
| -------------------- | ----------------- | ----------------- |
| Uses External Data   | âœ…                | âŒ               |
| Model Weights Change | âŒ                | âœ…               |
| Cost                 | Lower             | Higher            |
| Easy to Update       | Yes               | Hard              |
| Best For             | Dynamic knowledge | Behavioral change |

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ¯ Key Takeaways

* RAG improves accuracy
* Uses embeddings + vector DB
* Reduces hallucination
* Supports private & real-time data
* Core component of modern Agentic AI systems
